<br>
Resisting the AoE Fear (Dragon Roar) has as much to do with level as it does with MR.  You can be higher level with less MR than average and still resist the fear.  I think that a Mage is not an asset to the group against Naggy until lvl 49 ... before then, you will feel like you didn't contribute a single thing  except for taking mana from a Cleric to rez you.  Even at lvl 49, I felt quite useless against Naggy ...  the only contribution I've ever made against Naggy is the damage done by my pet and the Mod Rods I summoned after the battle to help with the rezzing.  Other than that, I felt like an underpowered Wizzy who couldn't stick a nuke.<br>
<br>
Gathering your gear early is a good idea though ... and the thread posted above by Gurron should help you out.<br>
